  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (MRL 3)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. This package reflects an elevated Model Risk Level 3 determination following regulatory feedback that the device's novel impeller geometry introduces higher uncertainty than originally scoped. Twelve of thirteen credibility factors are fully assessed and meet required levels. The 'Use error' factor is recorded as not-assessed on the basis that user-interaction risks are considered irrelevant to a purely computational workflow; however, this rationale conflates applicability with assessment and the factor has not been formally scoped out or designated not-applicable.",
